’s an honor for us to be a gartner cool vendor we are proud of our innovation and its positive impact on our global customers” said nozomi networks ceo edgard capdevielle “we believe this is strong validation of the strength of our product and its proven value to customers around the globe our employees are gratified to see nozomi networks recognized by gartner and know technology executives and boards can rely on gartner for valuable insights” leveraging artificial intelligence and machine learning nozomi networks has created a single platform for comprehensive ics cybersecurity with tens of thousands of industrial devices secured around the world it combines anomaly detection vulnerability assessment and asset inventory into one solution that secures critical infrastructure operations amid rising global threats in addition to the gartner news the company today announced it has added global chief marketing officer kim legelis and vice president of business development chet namboodri to the company’s management team both bring deep experience and valuable business relationships in industrial networking and ics security forged during their previous tenures with cisco systems ge lockheed martin industrial defender and symantec since announcing a  million series a funding round in october nozomi networks has seen better than expected market growth in both north america and europe in march nozomi networks announced a new release of scadaguardian delivering the industry’s most comprehensive solution for both operational visibility and ics cybersecurity the company exceeded its q forecast for customer growth strengthened key partnerships with fortinet and check point and expanded its overall partner program to more than a dozen integrators the company has deployed its technologies globally to leaders in key industries such as oil power generation nuclear energy and manufacturing beyond customer expansion industry accolades continue to accumulate nozomi networks was recognized at the rsa conference as cyber defense magazine’s cutting edge icsscada security solution winner the company won the popular vote in this year’s cybersecurity excellence awards and just last week nozomi networks was named a red herring top  north america finalist “when we moved corporate headquarters to san francisco and added edgard capdevielle to the team in october we expected it to be a solid year for nozomi networks” said cofounder and chief product officer andrea carcano “the progress we’ve made so far has exceeded our expectations i believe this latest recognition from gartner as well as significant customer growth and the industry talent joining our team is a testament to the strength of our company our product and our vision and an indicator of much more to come in the months ahead” about nozomi networks nozomi networks is revolutionizing industrial control system ics cybersecurity with the most comprehensive platform to deliver realtime cybersecurity and operational visibility since  the company has innovated the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence to meet the unique challenges of critical infrastructure operations nozomi networks delivers both cybersecurity and process anomaly detection along with industrial network visualization and monitoring asset inventory and vulnerability assessment deployed in the world’s largest industrial installations customers benefit from enhanced cybersecurity and improved operational reliability with one endtoend solution nozomi networks is headquartered in san francisco california  wwwnozominetworkscom gartner disclaimer gartner does not endorse any vendor product or service depicted in our research publications and does not advise technology users to select only those vendors with the highest ratings or other designation  gartner research publications consist of the opinions of gartners research organization and should not be construed as statements of fact  gartner disclaims all warranties expressed o